title: Yulia Svyrydenko - Wikipedia
snippet: Yulia Anatoliivna Svyrydenko (Ukrainian: Юлія Анатоліївна Свириденко, IPA: [ˈjul⁽ʲ⁾ijɐ ɐnɐˈtɔl⁽ʲ⁾ijiu̯nɐ swɪrɪˈdɛnko]; born 25 December 1985) is a Ukrainian politician who has served as the 19th prime minister of Ukraine since 17 July 2025.

title: Yulia Svyrydenko: Government's Winter Support continues | Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine
snippet: Department of Information and Public Communications of the Secretariat of the Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine, posted 16 December 2025 15:54 ... Government winter support continues, emphasized Ukrainian Prime Minister Yulia Svyrydenko.

title: Yulia Svyrydenko: Government adopts decision to allocate an additional UAH 400 million to support people released from russian captivity | Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine
snippet: The Government has decided to allocate an additional UAH 400 million to support people released from russian captivity, as well as the families of those who are still in captivity.

title: Yulia Svyrydenko: Government approves a series of decisions to support people with disabilities | Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine
snippet: Department of Information and Public Communications of the Secretariat of the Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine, posted 17 December 2025 19:36 ... Today, at its session, the Government approved a series of decisions to support people with disabilities...

title: Yulia Svyrydenko held working meeting with Prime Minister of Portugal Luis Montenegro | Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine
snippet: Prime Minister of Ukraine Yulia Svyrydenko held a working meeting with Prime Minister of Portugal Luís Montenegro, to discuss key areas of bilateral cooperation, including defense, economy, and energy security.
